<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6638> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6638" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Author of a Lex Licinia, probably tribunicial, and later than the Lex Aebutia (see above), which barred the relatives of a man who established an office from serving in it. It must precede 63 (Cic. Leg. Agr. 2.21; cf. Dom. 51)." .
